{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b419db4c-aa26-4344-b938-1a628935288e","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .dmp file! Unfortunately, I don't have a specialized skill for **analyzing** crash dumps (the `dump-collect` skill is only for *collecting* them).\n\nHere's how to analyze it:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (recommended for .NET apps):\n\n```bash\n# Install the tool if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\nOnce inside the interactive session, useful commands:\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show the last exception |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack -all` | Stacks for all threads |\n| `dso` | Dump stack objects |\n| `gcroot <addr>` | Trace object roots |\n\n**Typical workflow:**\n1. `pe` — see if there's an unhandled exception\n2. `threads` — find the faulting thread\n3. `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — inspect it\n\nWould you like me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file interactively? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fe21ca25-996a-4705-9b14-fde9e6fe2cd9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants help analyzing it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - This is for capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstones, not .dmp files\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files. Since the `dump-collect` skill explicitly prohibits analyzing dumps, I'll need to guide the user on how to analyze the dump using standard tools like WinDbg or dotnet-dump.","outputTokens":544,"requestId":"C3C2:AF6EC:1DB1B43:2149050:6A07C3AD"},"id":"8ce0510b-6b5e-4a98-8d87-8aea813eed95","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:09:14.293Z","parentId":"3dce840e-6b84-44c4-84e5-4afcecffee29"}
